comments: Konchar (MEM) brings his left hand to the ball and incidental contact occurs when Wagner (ORL) rips through to start his drive.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) gives a step of distance when establishing himself in Black's (ORL) path and marginal contact occurs during the backscreen.
Williams Jr. (MEM) is moving alongside Banchero's (ORL) path and marginal body contact occurs during Banchero's drive.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) steps backwards into Carter Jr.'s (ORL) right arm and initiates contact that affects his shot attempt near the basket.
Wagner (ORL) briefly clamps Williams' (MEM) arm and releases before he is able to control the rebound.
Isaac (ORL) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact after Jackson Jr. (MEM) gathers to move into his upward shooting motion.
Banchero's (ORL) arm is in a vertical position when incidental arm contact occurs with Jackson Jr. (MEM).
Carter Jr. (ORL) brings his right hand forward and cleanly blocks Jackson Jr.'s (MEM) shot attempt near the rim.

Replay review of the foul called on Williams (MEM) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful.  Williams is in a legal guarding position during Wagner's (ORL) drive to the basket, but Williams Jr. (MEM) reaches in and initiates illegal contact with Wagner's right arm.  A foul is assessed to Williams Jr.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) establishes himself in Black's (ORL) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Issac (ORL) briefly brings his left hand toward the ball and brushes Kennard's (MEM) arm as he releases the pass.
The shot clock expires while Memphis is still in possession of the ball.
Konchar (MEM) legally contests Ingles's (ORL) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
